ON PEDAGOGICAL OVERREACH IN LARGE LANGUAGE MODELS
A FORMAL INQUIRY INTO THE CLAIM THAT A STATISTICAL TEXT ENGINE CAN “TEACH ALMOST ANYTHING ON EARTH,” INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO BRAIN SURGERY, GAS SAFETY, STRUCTURAL LOAD-BEARING, and OTHER ACTIVITIES WITH REGRETTABLE CONSEQUENCES WHEN IMPROVISED

