7. A Taxonomy of Things the Model Can Help With Versus Things It Cannot Confer

7.1 Legitimate Educational Use

The model may be reasonably useful for:
	•	clarifying terminology,
	•	comparing concepts,
	•	generating practice questions,
	•	explaining beginner principles,
	•	summarizing readings,
	•	offering analogies,
	•	helping formulate study plans,
	•	rehearsing oral explanations,
	•	and identifying areas for further professional training.

7.2 Illegitimate Capability Transfer

The model should not be treated as conferring:
	•	licensure,
	•	supervised clinical judgment,
	•	code compliance,
	•	field-ready competence,
	•	procedural sign-off,
	•	situational awareness under pressure,
	•	duty of care,
	•	or bodily skill acquisition by eloquence alone.

This paper notes with concern that public enthusiasm frequently jumps from the first list to the second by pure vibes.

